Preheat the oven to 220 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @water{} to the boil with @salt{½%tsp}.

Dismantle the @butternut squash{1} by chopping it in half widthways to separate the top from the
bulb at the bottom. Then put the flat part of each half on the #chopping board{}. Slice downwards to
remove the skin. Chop the bulb in half widthways and remove the seeds with a #spoon{}. Finally chop
half the squash into 2cm cubes. Pick the leaves from two large sprigs of @rosemary{2} and finely
chop.

Place the butternut squash and half the chopped rosemary on a large #baking tray{} and toss together
with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{½%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Pop in the oven for
~{20-25%mins} or until the squash is well cooked and starting to crisp at the edges.

Meanwhile, peel and cut the @onion{1} and chop into ½cm pieces. Peel and finely chop the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Pick the @sage{1%stem} leaves and roughly chop them too.

Add the @wholewheat penne{500%g} to the boiling water and cook for ~{10%mins}. Drain, reserving
all the cooking water, then transfer the cooked pasta to a large #ovenproof dish{}.

While the pasta is cooking, heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} over a medium heat and add your
onion. Cook for ~{3%mins} until slightly softened, then add the @pancetta{2%British smoked bacon lardons},
garlic, chopped sage and remaining rosemary. Leave to cook, stirring occasionally, for about
~{5-6%mins} or until the pancetta is crispy.

> Be careful not to let the herbs burn!

Carefully transfer the herby pancetta mixture to the same ovenproof dish as the pasta. Now add your
@ricotta cheese{1}, @baby spinach{3}(picked), squash (which should now be cooked), 250ml of the
reserved pasta water and @salt{½%tsp} to the ovenproof dish too. Carefully combine to form a nice
creamy pasta mixture.

> Feel free to add a little more water if you like!

In a #small bowl{}, quickly mix together the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g},
@panko breadcrumbs{1 cup} and a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Generously cover the pasta
dish with this cheesy crumb topping, drizzle with a good splash of @olive oil{} and return to the
oven for ~{5%mins}. Voilà, dinner is served!

> Adults, if you like things hot, don't forget to add your chilli flakes here!